SIMPLE: long-waisted
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Long-waisted
<hw>Long"-waist`ed</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Having a long waist; long from the armpits to the bottom of the
waist; -- said of persons.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Long from the part about the neck or shoulder, or
from the armpits, to the bottom of the weist, or to the skirt; -- said
of garments; <as>as, a <ex>long-waisted</ex> coat</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Longways</ent>⟦br⟧
